          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1632217495518-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to the pan with the <strong>mild curry paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1632217499558-x200.jpg",
